comments.comment:
Shout out to our whole team!! 
Crazy tough project and so fun! 
Which shot was your favorite? 
- Coby & the dudes
This format of adding in clips of interviewing the guys makes the video so much better, and I'm sure a lot of people would agree. Keeps the viewer engaged even more than they already were.
Showing the failures makes for way better storytelling and content than only showing the successes. Keep this up!
That drone footage of the soccer ball was top notch. Nice flying.
Easily my favorite Dude Perfect video. The storytelling and character development was so much better! Love the format.
I’ll give Ty a lot of credit on the arrow shot. The fatigue from that draw weight is nuts. And the amount of luck needed with the wind. Congrats on that one!
15 years of trick shots, Dude Perfect still doing the impossible

13:44 
Ty: “It’s a NAAAGHH!”
Sparky: “nyeh.”

Conversions for the measurements for the rest of the shots: 

1/16 mile: 100 m
1/10 mile: 160 m
1/8 mile: 200 m
1/3 mile: 540 m
1/2 mile: 800 m
2 miles: 3.2 km
I really like this format. Showing the grit to do this, in a time of youtube doubt. Awesome job guys.
Garrett saying ‘So they called me’ and then making the shot is as cold as it gets.

I came back to Dude Perfect after a while and I have to say I enjoy every bit of it. I respect the compassion of the crew toward each other, willing to give up a trick shot in recognition to one of the member's broken fingers, but also the comedy and jokes the crew have with each other is just the cherry on top. You guys keep going and do what you think is best. Much love.
“He threw a selfie.” Is a genius quote. I love Sparky
Please do more videos like this where you show the process, not just the final result! It makes it so much more entertaining and we can feel excited when it finally goes in.
24:18 Imagine if that basketball didn't go in
“This is why we won so easily in 1776”
The calendar edits were awesome
Garrett’s “so they called me”was cold 1:24
King of 2 miles shooting! Cool to see these guys get hooked up with us precision rifle shooters

When it cut to the cameraman doing his job during the golf shot there was a split second where I thought to myself, "calm down, you aren't the one swinging a club a hundred times" and then he talks about needing every shot to be in focus and centered and I felt so humbled. Those cameramen are almost pure focus all day long and that's dedication.
